  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Accountant",
  "description": "<p><strong>MAIN RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong></p><p></p><p>· To provide a pro-active and efficient Accounts service to Singapore entities</p><p>· Compliance to Monthly Reporting Timetable, Finance Manual and Company Policies.</p><p>· Working closely with Senior Accountant and Finance Manager for effective management and control from a financial perspective.</p><p>· Preparation of monthly management accounts (CVR), variance analysis reporting Balance sheet reconciliation and other reports as required</p><p>· Ensure timely submission of month end report to Group</p><p>· Monthly reconciliation of intercompany transactions</p><p>· Manage finance team (AR,AP,GL) and ensure finance operation is running efficiently</p><p>· Cash flow compliance and reporting.</p><p>· Ownership of proper tax compliances and filing for both direct and indirect taxes in the entities assigned.</p><p>· Collate and review, monthly and year end reconciliation of local entity statutory results to group reporting ensuring that differences, if any, are approved, adequately documented and appropriate</p><p>· Key contact with external auditors and internal auditors in planning, executing and completing audits for the assigned entity/entities.</p><p>· Support budgeting process and participation in other group and regional initiatives.</p><p>· Any additional duties assigned as required.</p><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><p>· Tertiary Qualification in Finance, Accounting.</p><p>· CPA certification is preferred.</p><p>· Preferably 5+ years of relevant experience.</p><p>· Strong analytical skills, attention to detail and accuracy</p><p>· Able to prioritize and work to tight timeframes</p><p>· Positive attitude and a great team player</p><p>· Previous experience in project accounting will be highly regarded</p><p>· Competent with Microsoft applications including Outlook, Word and Excel</p><p>· Able to start work immediately.</p>",
